Title#1: 5MT-3 Area 3 drawings: Note from Rich Wilshusen
Name#1: University of Colorado Museum of Natural History
Abstract#1: This document is a note from Rich Wilshusen on the drawings done at the Yellow Jacket archeological dig site, section 5MT-3 area 3. The note reads, "There were two notebooks of groundstone notes and tracings for Area 3. They are marked by the different tabs (House 3 #11,000 and 13,000 vs. metates, abrading stones, etc.) and classification systems (numbers vs. types of groundstone) in this new notebook. It is not clear whether there is overlap in the items documented, whether there is a single analytical framework, or why the notebooks were distinct. I will leave it to greater minds to unravel this. -RHW"
